## Current Role

I'm a Research Assistant at The George Institute for Global Health, embedded in the Critical Care team. My primary project is [SEPSIS SUPPORT](https://www.georgeinstitute.org/our-research/research-projects/post-sepsis-care-co-designed-models-of-support-sepsis-support) -- an NHMRC-funded program co-designing the first targeted models of post-sepsis care in Australia. Sepsis affects around 55,000 Australians each year, yet support after hospital discharge remains critically limited. The project brings together survivors, clinicians, and caregivers to change that.

